04831nam a22007455i 9780226718002DE-B159720210824034702.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210824t20212021ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a2020030495  a97802267180027 a10.7208/97802267180022doi  a(DE-B1597)571674  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL00aN66b.G76 2020 4aN66b.G766 2020 7aART0000002bisacsh04a700.12231 aGrootenboer, Hanneke, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Pensive Image :bArt as a Form of Thinking /cHanneke Grootenboer. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (240 p.) :b16 color plates, 26 halftones  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tArt as a Form of Thinking -- tPart I: Defining the Pensive Image -- tChapter 1 Theorizing Stillness -- tChapter 2 Tracing the Denkbild -- tPart II: Painting as Philosophical Reflection -- tChapter 3 Room for Reflection: Interior and Interiority -- tChapter 4 The Profundity of Still Life -- tChapter 5 Painting as a Space for Thought -- tPainting’s Wonder -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhile the philosophical dimension of painting has long been discussed, a clear case for painting as a form of visual thinking has yet to be made. Traditionally, vanitas still life paintings are considered to raise ontological issues while landscapes direct the mind towards introspection. Grootenboer moves beyond these considerations to focus on what remains unspoken in painting, the implicit and inexpressible that manifests in a quality she calls pensiveness. Different from self-aware or actively desiring images, pensive images are speculative, pointing beyond interpretation. An alternative pictorial category, pensive images stir us away from interpretation and toward a state of suspension where thinking through and with the image can start. In fluid prose, Grootenboer explores various modalities of visual thinking— as the location where thought should be found, as a refuge enabling reflection, and as an encounter that provokes thought. Through these considerations, she demonstrates that art works serve as models for thought as much as they act as instruments through which thinking can take place. Starting from the premise that painting is itself a type of thinking, The Pensive Image argues that art is capable of forming thoughts and shaping concepts in visual terms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aArt, ModernxHistory. 0aPaintingxPhilosophy. 0aPainting, ModernxHistory. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  a17th century Dutch art.  aaesthetics.  aart and contemplation.  aart and interiority.  aart and thought.  aart as thinking.  aart.  aphilosophy.  asister arts.  atranshistorical.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2021z9783110753783oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226718002423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226718002.jpg  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075403-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architec